Experiment-4 : Jenkins installation and setup, explore the Environment 
 
Step-1: Visit official website : https://www.jenkins.io 
-open jenkins
-click on windows
jenkins debian package
this is the debian package repository on jenkins to automate installations and upgrade to use repositry.
add the key to your system for the weekly release.
step-2: then add a jenkins apt repository entry.
step-3: update your local package index, then finally install jenkins.
step-4: the apt packages were signed using the key.
step-5: you will need to explicity a supported java runtime environment either from distribution.

As I am using ubantu OS – I will select Unantu/Debian 
 
-Now run all these commands in your terminal  
So, after running all the above commands , Jenkins will be installed in your system 
To start jenkins not run below command: 
sudo systemctl start Jenkins 
To see Jenkins is active or not run below command: 
sudo systemctl status Jenkins 
 
-Now above one is the password to open Jenkins , now minimize terminal 
and open any web browser and type https://localhost:8080 to open Jenkins 
 
-Enter password  
getting started 
 
-Select – install suggested plugins 
 
You can give user name And password, remember username and password because you 
need to enter it , when ever you open jekins. by default I am giving user name as admin 
and password as admin 

This is your Jenkins home page 
-click on save and finish. 
-click on start using jenkins. 
-If you want to uninstall Jenkins , you can use below commands: 
sudo service jenkins stop 
sudo systemctl stop jenkins 
sudo apt-get remove jenkins 
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/jenkins 
sudo rm -rf /var/lib/jenkins 
sudo userdel jenk
